  <summary date="2021-07-14T18:01:30Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Fair Access to Banking Act 

This bill restricts certain banks, credit unions, and payment card networks from refusing to do business with a person who is in compliance with the law. Restrictions include prohibiting the use of certain lending programs, initiating the process of terminating an institution's depository insurance, and instituting specified civil penalties.</summary>
